{
  "stem": "210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were also not home when they took the people on street.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they took them together with us at the same.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I figured out, you know, in order-- when we went to Auschwitz at that time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when they took us to the train, so we were together with my, my, the one that I worked for, with his cousin and her, her two children, her two daughters, because her husband was already not alive anymore either.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And everyday in the ghetto, you saw people laying dead.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the time, you know, with swollen bellies.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The children were not there anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Young people were not there anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Older people, you could see them always laying in the street.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they always used to go around with the wagons and pick up all the deads.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when this-- they liquidated the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At that time, they took me to-- took about three days, that we wound up in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And at that time, I told you that I took the name because I didn't want to be separated from-- so I figured when they going to ask me what my name is and all this.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in order, because, I-- my name with a K, and they were the A, so in order for us to be together, so I said my name is Adler.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Anyway, when we got out on the other side, they weren't there anymore anyway.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the, the, the cousins from my chief which had two daughters were together with me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, they over there-- I don't have to explain to you how it was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Go here, go there.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
